Title: An Efficient Delay-Constrained Minimum Spanning Tree Heuristic  
Author: H.F. Salama D.S. Reeves Y. Viniotis 
Affiliation: ECE and CSC Departments, N.C. State University  
Abstract: We study the delay-constrained minimum spanning tree problem in directed networks. This problem is NP-complete. Therefore, we propose an efficient heuristic to solve it. Simulation results under realistic networking conditions show that our heuristic's performance is close to optimal when the link loads are symmetric as well as when asymmetric link loads are used. 
